  "text": "SHMT2 is located not only in mitochondria but also in the cytoplasm, as shown by our data and those from other studies [CITATION_1] . SHMT2 is a tetrameric metabolic enzyme involved in one-carbon metabolism and can also participate in the BRISC-SHMT complex to deubiquitinate IFNAR1 and regulate interferon responses [CITATION_2] . In our study, SHMT2 regulated autophagy not by controlling one-carbon metabolism but by binding to cytoplasmic p53.",
